<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4114: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to">Cunningham</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-11T18:00:00-05:00">February 11, 1932—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>15. Your 33, February 11, 4 p.m. I authorize you, in your discretion, to
                            protest as from your Government, against all flying of any airplanes,
                            whether Chinese or Japanese, in military service, over the International
                            Settlement and again to protest against any use whatever, by either
                            disputant, of any part of the Settlement as a base or channel in
                            connection with military operations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>